                <p>The name Nikola Tesla conjures images of lightning bolts, wireless energy transmission, and revolutionary inventions that shaped our modern world. Yet among his many achievements and eccentricities, one particular fascination has captured the imagination of millions: his alleged obsession with the numbers 3, 6, and 9. The internet is flooded with claims about Tesla's "369 theory," complete with the tantalizing quote: "If you only knew the magnificence of the 3, 6, and 9, then you would have a key to the universe."</p>

