                <h2>The Science Behind Tesla's Vision</h2>

                <p>Tesla's genius lay in his ability to understand and manipulate the fundamental forces of nature. His resonance theory-using the matching of frequencies to create energetic vibration-was demonstrated through his famous Tesla coil and nearly caused the collapse of his New York laboratory building.</p>

                <p>His Wardenclyffe towers were designed to use Earth's natural resonance frequency to transmit energy wirelessly on a planetary scale. The project was designed, tested, and ultimately canceled by capitalist forces at the last moment.</p>

                <p>Tesla theorized that energy-based power in the universe materializes with specific vibrations and has a frequency value, and if you change that frequency, the energy of that object will also change. According to him, this concept wasn't limited to physical things-it was valid for metaphysical things as well. He believed that conscious beings and even their thoughts could be changed through this power.</p>

                <h2>Modern Scientific Validation: String Theory</h2>

                <p>Tesla's vision has found remarkable validation in modern physics. In the late 20th century, physicists like Gabriel Veneziano, Leonard Susskind, and Michael Green developed string theory-proposing that the fundamental building blocks of matter are not atoms or even subatomic particles, but vibrating energy strings.</p>

