                <h2>The Rise of Vortex Mathematics and the Rodin Connection</h2>

                <p>The Tesla 3-6-9 myth gained additional momentum through its association with "Vortex Based Mathematics" (VBM), developed by Marko Rodin. This mathematical system, which Rodin claims reveals the "Mathematical Fingerprint of God," heavily features the numbers 3, 6, and 9.</p>

                <p>Rodin's work involves creating patterns with numbers arranged in circles, focusing on digital roots (reducing multi-digit numbers to single digits through addition). When following specific sequences-such as repeatedly doubling numbers and reducing them to digital roots-the pattern 1-2-4-8-7-5 repeats infinitely, never including 3, 6, or 9.</p>

                <p>From this observation, Rodin and his followers conclude that 3, 6, and 9 exist in a higher dimension and control the physical world. However, mainstream mathematicians and scientists have thoroughly debunked these claims.</p>

                <h2>The Scientific Reality Behind the Pattern</h2>

                <p>The mathematical patterns that form the foundation of vortex mathematics are indeed real, but their significance is far more mundane than claimed. As explained by mathematics educators, these patterns emerge naturally from our base-10 number system and modular arithmetic.</p>

                <p>The reason 3, 6, and 9 don't appear in the doubling sequence's digital roots is simply a consequence of mathematical properties specific to base-10. In any other numerical base, different numbers would exhibit these "special" properties. For instance, in base-8, the number 7 would demonstrate similar characteristics.</p>

                <p>RationalWiki aptly describes vortex mathematics as "pseudomathematical/vaguely theological pile of nonsense," noting that such patterns "pop up all the time in mathematics, because mathematics is basically just the rigorous study of patterns."</p>

